# Arduino NRF24 Servo Control Project

## Overview

This project is a wireless transmitter and receiver system using Arduino, NRF24L01 modules, a joystick, a push button, an LED, and a servo motor.

The transmitter reads joystick movement and button status, then sends the data wirelessly using the NRF24L01 module.

The receiver gets the data, controls the servo motor angle based on the joystick position, and turns the LED on or off depending on the button state.

## Features

* Wireless communication using NRF24L01
* Joystick control for servo angle
* Push button control for LED
* Real-time data transmission
* Servo motor movement from 0 to 180 degrees
* LED ON/OFF control using button press

## Components Used

* 2x Arduino boards
* 2x NRF24L01 modules
* 1x Joystick module
* 1x Servo motor
* 1x LED
* 1x Resistor for LED
* Jumper wires
* Breadboard

## Technologies Used

* Arduino IDE
* C++
* SPI Library
* RF24 Library
* Servo Library

## How It Works

### Transmitter

* Reads joystick X-axis value
* Reads push button state
* Maps joystick value to servo angle (0–180)
* Sends the packet using NRF24L01

### Receiver

* Receives data packet
* Moves servo motor to the received angle
* Turns LED ON when button is pressed
* Turns LED OFF when button is released

## Purpose

This project was created to demonstrate wireless communication between two Arduino devices and real-time control of hardware components using NRF24L01 modules.

